questions.scenario:
You are debugging a race condition in a high-concurrency Spring Boot service. A senior developer wrote the following code to ensure atomic updates to a database-backed inventory system:

java
@Service
public class StockService {
    @Autowired
    private InventoryRepository repository;

    @Transactional
    public synchronized void reduceStock(Long productId, int amount) {
        Inventory item = repository.findById(productId).orElseThrow();
        if (item.getQuantity() >= amount) {
            item.setQuantity(item.getQuantity() - amount);
            repository.save(item);
        }
    }
}

Despite the `synchronized` keyword, the database shows inconsistent stock levels under heavy load (over-selling).
